<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-04-11T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-04-11T00:00:00-05:00" n="412" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d412">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 422.11G93/749.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Arbitrator</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">President</gloss>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Extract.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-04-11">
                                    <hi rend="italic">April 11, 1914</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: As the Arbitrator named by you under
                            Article 27 of the contract dated June 14th, 1897, between the Republic
                            of Ecuador and the Guayaquil and Quito Railway Company, to settle in
                            conjunction with the Arbitrator named by the President of Ecuador all
                            controversies or disagreements existing between the contracting parties,
                            I have the honor to report that after a month spent in Quito in
                            prolonged conferences and negotiations with the Ecuadorian Arbitrator,
                            we have not been able to agree.* * *</p>
                        <p>Respectfully,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">A. L. Miller</hi></signed>.</closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>